# Dashboard grid layout

Permanent rules for all dashboard layout and edit-mode work in `style.css`, `widgets.js`, `app.js`, and `index.html`. Do not deviate.

## The grid

- CSS grid on `.dashboard-grid` in `style.css` with `--grid-columns: 36`.
- Each widget occupies `{ col, row, colSpan, rowSpan }` in grid units.
- Layout persisted in `localStorage` key `networkMonitor.dashboard.layout` as `{ version: 23, widgets: { [id]: { col, row, colSpan, rowSpan } }, summaryCards: [] }`. Do not rename key or envelope.
- Grid lines are cell boundaries. `--dashboard-grid-gap` is `0px` on `.dashboard-grid` — never change track gap.

## The gap between panels

- **`--widget-panel-inset: 8px`** in `:root` is the **only** visual gutter between panels.
- Applied via `margin: var(--widget-panel-inset)` on `.dashboard-grid > .widget, .dashboard-grid > .chart-wrap` — never per-widget hardcoding.
- JS reads inset via `getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)` / `getWidgetPanelInsetPx()` — never duplicate the value in JS.
- Snapping targets grid lines only; inset is render-time margin, never in snap math.
- Adjacent panels never visually touch (each panel inset from owned cell boundary).

## Minimum size

- `measureWidgetMinSpans()` derives min `colSpan`/`rowSpan` from DOM scroll sizes.
- Content must fit **rendered** area: `renderedSpanPixels = allocatedSpan - 2 * inset` (`renderedSpanPixels()`, `minSpanForRenderedPixels()`).
- Resize stops at minimum; overlap rejected via `placementsOverlap` / `findOverlappingWidget`.

## Content scaling

- Widget interiors size to rendered area (cell minus inset): flex, `min-height: 0`, Chart.js `maintainAspectRatio: false`.
- Chart canvases fill containers — no hardcoded pixel dimensions on dashboard charts.
- **Dashboard grid children** must use `height: auto` and `max-height: calc(100% - 2 * var(--widget-panel-inset))` on `.dashboard-grid > .widget` and `.chart-wrap` variants. **Never** `height: 100%` on those selectors — it overflows inset and panels touch.

## Moving (edit mode only)

- Drag by panel title/header (`.widget-panel-title`, `.chart-panel-title`) or `.widget-drag-handle`.
- On release: snap to nearest grid cell origin via `pointerToGridPlacement`.
- Overlap rejected — no swap, no reflow of other widgets.

## Edit mode vs view mode

- **View mode (default):** no move/resize; layout via `stackMeasureAndApplyDashboardLayout` + `DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_STACK` (two-pass measure/apply — do not break or bypass). Do **not** call stack measure during edit mode. Refit saves to localStorage when row spans change.
- **Edit mode:** `#widget-grid-edit-btn` in the Customize dashboard dialog only (no header Edit layout button). Apply: `#grid-edit-apply-btn`. Cancel: `#grid-edit-cancel-btn`.

### Entering edit mode

- Grid overlay on `.dashboard-grid::before` behind panels.
- Panels semi-transparent (`opacity: 0.82`); inset keeps grid lines visible at seams.
- Eight resize handles: `n`, `s`, `e`, `w`, `ne`, `nw`, `se`, `sw`.
- Headers draggable (`cursor: grab`).
- Fire `dashboard:grid-edit-mode` with `{ detail: { active: true } }`.

### While in edit mode

- Mutations go to `gridEditLayoutDraft` only — **no localStorage** until Apply.
- Snapshot in `gridEditLayoutSnapshot` at entry for Cancel restore.
- Min spans enforced during drag/resize; overlap rejected in real time (resize preview skips invalid placements).
- On Apply: `WidgetDashboard.saveLayout(gridEditLayoutDraft)`, exit, restore full opacity, remove handles.
- On Cancel: discard draft, `applyDashboardPlacementsOnly(gridEditLayoutSnapshot)` — exact restore, no stack repack.

### Exiting edit mode

- Fire `dashboard:grid-edit-mode` with `{ detail: { active: false } }`.
- Chart.js axis grids toggle **only** via this event (and `getDashboardChartGridOptions()` at chart creation).

## Layout versioning

- `LAYOUT_VERSION` is `23`. Increment on default layout or migration changes; add step in `migrateLayoutVersion`.

## Chart.js grid visibility (`app.js`)

- `applyDashboardChartGridVisibility` must be defined **before** `buildChart()` (TDZ).
- **Do not** call it from inside `buildChart()` after `chart.update()` — causes `t.startsWith is not a function`.
- Toggle only via `dashboard:grid-edit-mode` listener and `getDashboardChartGridOptions()` at creation.

## Non-negotiable invariants

- All widget content visible and contained at minimum size and above; no unexpected clip/overflow/scroll.
- No two panels visually touch or overlap in any mode.
- `--widget-panel-inset` defined once in `:root` only.
- `app.js` and `widgets.js` stay monolithic — do not split into modules.
- `window.WidgetDashboard` exported API is stable.
- After web file changes: rebuild `ConnectWatch.exe` and hard-refresh browser (Ctrl+F5) — assets are embedded; stale process serves old files.
